Introduction

NJZ, formerly NewJeans, is a South Korean girl group. Formed by ADOR, they debuted on July 22, 2022, with the single "Attention". On November 28, 2024, NewJeans said in a late-night press conference that they would be departing from their agency, ADOR. On February 6, 2025, it was announced through the press that NewJeans would be rebranded to NJZ along with new profile photos.

NJZ announced that they would pause all activities for a while due to the court's decision.
